quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  26,176,The inhabitants of Aykah impugned the apostles
  26,177,"when Shu‘ayb said to them, ‘Will you not be wary [of Allah]"
  26,178,"Indeed I am a trusted apostle [sent] to you"
  26,179,So be wary of Allah and obey me
  26,180,I do not ask you any reward for it; my reward lies only with the Lord of all the worlds
  26,181,"Observe the full measure, and do not be of those who give short measure"
  26,182,Weigh with an even balance
  26,183,"and do not cheat the people of their goods. Do not act wickedly on the earth, causing corruption"
  26,184,Be wary of Him who created you and the earlier generations.’
  26,185,"They said, ‘Indeed you are one of the bewitched"
  26,186,"You are just a human being like us, and we indeed consider you to be a liar"
  26,187,"Make a fragment of the sky falls upon us, should you be truthful.’"
  26,188,"He said, ‘My Lord knows best what you are doing.’"
  26,189,"So they impugned him, and then they were overtaken by the punishment of the day of the overshadowing cloud. It was indeed the punishment of a terrible day"
  26,190,There is indeed a sign in that; but most of them do not have faith
  26,191,"Indeed your Lord is the All-mighty, the All-merciful"